</taxonomicName>
is the earliest name for 
<taxonomicName id="E9B1E01B6F51177FB01E02018C55463B" authority="Boiss. Following Stearn" authorityName="Boiss. Following Stearn" authorityYear="1882" class="Liliopsida" family="Amaryllidaceae" genus="Allium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hierochuntinum">
<emphasis id="BC8096EA712B92FC4AFF42F4EDB14C69" italics="true" pageNumber="276">A. hierochuntinum</emphasis>
Boiss. Following Stearn
</taxonomicName>
(in 
<emphasis id="471E4EC5BCA8AFE22377202A07B937A9" italics="true" pageNumber="276">Bull. Brit. Mus. (Nat. Hist.), Bot.</emphasis>
2: 181. 1960), he informally rejected the former because it has been applied more or less continuously since 1762 to a well-known cultivar of 
<taxonomicName id="212D48A8854D90BEAD80CCCC0BFB6A6E" authority="L. However" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Liliopsida" family="Amaryllidaceae" genus="Allium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cepa">
<emphasis id="3DF860EAE0CF0CA138C3A04D23EDDD6D" italics="true" pageNumber="276">A. cepa</emphasis>
L. However
</taxonomicName>
, no formal rejection proposal has been made.
</paragraph>
